<TITLE> Bosnia should rush to EU because of Kosovo:envoy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SARAJEVO, Feb 7 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Bosnia should move faster to secure EU membership as a safeguard against a possible crisis in Serbia's breakaway province of Kosovo, international peace envoy told the Oslobodjenje daily on Thursday. Miroslav Lajcak also said Bosnian leaders should focus on the issues crucial for closer EU ties and stop bickering at a time when political instability related to Kosovo's expected independence clouded the region. UN-administrated province of Kosovo is expected to declare independence from Serbia this month, a pattern that Bosnian Serb leaders have threatened to follow if the survival of their part of Bosnia, the Serb Republic, was jeopardised. "The relation between Bosnia and Kosovo is another obvious reason why Bosnia needs to find its place within the European structures," Lajcak told the Sarajevo daily in an interview. "It is irresponsible towards the state to slow down the road towards the Union, which is the only clear guarantor of ... stability in the region," the Slovak diplomat said. Muslim, Serb and Croat politicians failed last weekend to agree on how to proceed with reforms seen as key for the Balkan country's future relations with the EU. Lajcak has said signing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with the EU could be delayed until mid-2008 unless required police reforms were produced so
